<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-0357 </DOCNO><TEXT>After a presentation of Einstein's and Bohr's antagonistic point of viewon the interpretation of Quantum Mechanics an illustration of their conflictingpositions in the particular case of Young's double slit experiment ispresented. It is then shown that in their most recent form (i.e. timedependent neutron interferometry) these experiments suggest (if one acceptsabsolute energy-momentum conservation in all individual microprocesses)that Einstein was right in the Bohr-Einstein controversy.</TEXT></DOC>